Description: Body sherd of Chian black-figured Komast pottery chalice; white slip; interior glazed streaky black; part of spiked rosette in added white outline with added red centre; exterior: black-figure decoration consisting of komast to left, playing the aulos (head with part of turban in red remaining); part of incised rosette as filling ornament.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GD.1287) (phase 2)
